The Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai, who toured the crisis-ridden areas of Benue State last weekend expresses concern about the terrain which poses a major challenge to troops during swift response but he assured in this interview that the Nigerian Army was already building confidence in the people who fled their homes to return back. Buratai also posited that criminal elements have infiltrated the killings in the state from both sides of the local and armed herders.